28	to old day according to bruno's companion wibert bruno was killed by a duke of some part of prussia whereas netimer is called the king. the somebody suppose that they were laid in przemyl where some historians place bruno's diocese true such localization of the bruno's burial place is hardly probably because the przemyl area belonged to ortodox kievan rus in  and even until . annals of magdeburg thietmar of merseburg's chronicle works of magdeburg bishops annals of quedlinburg and many other written sources of xi-xv centuries recorded the story. soon after his death bruno and his companions were revered as martyrs and saint bruno was canonized bruno. 
